the story of a three-day pass ( french title la permission ) is a black-and-white film written and directed , often in a french new wave style , by melvin van peebles , based on a novel he wrote in french , la permission .   although made in 1967 , the film was not released in the u.s. until july 8 , 1968 .   van peebles also collaborated on the score with mickey baker and sings one of the two songs written for the film , " when my number gon na hit " .   the other song , " hard times " , is a man-woman duet ; one of the singers is mickey baker .